headline: Does Target’s SoHo Test Lab Redefine Its In-Store Experience Strategy For TGT Investors?
summary: Target Corporation recently opened its transformed Target SoHo concept store at 600 Broadway in New York City, creating an immersive, trend-led space that blends shopping with play, discovery and style-focused experiences. The SoHo store will serve as a testing ground through 2026 and beyond, allowing Target to trial rotating assortments, experiential zones and curated collaborations that could inform broader merchandising, design and in-store experience decisions across the chain.
